---
import { hasHeadshot } from '../lib/assets';
---

<div class:list={['about', { 'has-photo': hasHeadshot }]}>
  <div class="bio">
    <p>
      I’m a PhD student at UCL working on machine learning for nuclear fusion
      [FILL: group/centre name, supervisor if you want it listed]. My research
      focuses on time-series foundation models for plasma diagnostics:
      pretraining on large, heterogeneous tokamak signal data so that
      downstream tasks like [FILL: 1–2 concrete downstream tasks, e.g.
      disruption prediction / confinement-state classification] need far less
      labelled data.
    </p>
    <p>
      I previously worked on geometric generative modelling during my MSc at
      [FILL: institution].
    </p>
  </div>
  {
    // The photo appears automatically once public/headshot.jpg exists.
    hasHeadshot && (
      <img
        class="photo"
        src="/headshot.jpg"
        alt="Portrait of Lewis O’Donnell"
        width="168"
        height="210"
        loading="lazy"
        decoding="async"
      />
    )
  }
</div>

<style>
  .about {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
  }

  .about.has-photo {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .bio {
    columns: 2;
    column-gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .bio p {
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .bio p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .photo {
    width: 10.5rem;
    height: 13.125rem;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 1px solid var(--hairline);
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .bio {
      columns: 1;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about.has-photo {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .photo {
      order: -1;
      width: 8.5rem;
      height: 10.625rem;
    }
  }
</style>
